<div id="review_273932309" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/273932309" />
    <a title="Marc Weitz" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3577919-marc-weitz"><img alt="Marc Weitz" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1597225736p2/3577919.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/273932309?book_show_action=true">Feb 07, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Marc Weitz" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Marc Weitz" href="/user/show/3577919-marc-weitz">Marc Weitz</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer273932309" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1859269622385949929">Ever sat down with a friend for cocktails only to have them retell their same old stories without showing the slightest bit of interest in you? That was this book. This is the fourth book I&apos;ve read from this author, which means that I&apos;ve read all her books. Obviously, I&apos;ve enjoyed them, or I would not have bothered reading this one. But the author rehashes many stories from her first book &quot;Don&apos;t Lets Go to the Dogs Tonight,&quot; only this time from her parents&apos; perspective and without the in-depth d</span>
  <span id="freeText1859269622385949929" style="display:none">Ever sat down with a friend for cocktails only to have them retell their same old stories without showing the slightest bit of interest in you? That was this book. This is the fourth book I've read from this author, which means that I've read all her books. Obviously, I've enjoyed them, or I would not have bothered reading this one. But the author rehashes many stories from her first book "Don't Lets Go to the Dogs Tonight," only this time from her parents' perspective and without the in-depth descriptions or emotions. <br /><br />The author seemed to want to tell her parents' story, but I found that I don't care about her parents' story. This is the part where I felt the author didn't care about my needs. She just wanted to write a book about her parents, and we the reader better like it. <br /><br />There were new stories, but they weren't all that interesting. When Alexandra Fuller tells her stories about her life, she is at her best. Let's hope she hasn't run out.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1859269622385949929" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


